The completion progress was moved from the requirements table and placed in events. task.summary:
Fix Completion Progress Storage
Completion progress was being stored in the requirements table, however this table should be generic for use by all organizations at a given school. The completion progress was moved from the requirements table and placed in events. This way when an event is added to the system, the processing controller can calculate the amount of completion that the given event will yield, and save that to the database.
The main views have been updated to show all requirements as fully completed, the logic still needs to be added to compute actual completion.

Sum Event Progress
The main views now propperly query the database to sum the requirement_progress of all events related to the requirement at hand. The seeds file has been updated to show progress for the Service Hours requirement.

Provide Tier Status to User
The main controller now calculates the current tier expected for the group based on their progress towards requirements. An overview view shows the expected tier and the points until the next tier.
The numbering scheme for requirements has also been updated to correspond to the actual requirement section and number.
